    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AddCommand
    Command for adding one or more NetPBM image files to the active session.
    CloseCommand
    Command that removes a specific image from the active session by its file name.
    CollageCommand
    Command for creating a collage from two loaded images.
    Command
    A command that can be run from the console with arguments.
    CommandMenu
    Manages and dispatches all console commands in the image editor.
    CommandType
    Lists all available command types in the image editor.
    CreateRandomPPMImage
     
    ExitCommand
    Command that terminates the image editor application.
    GrayscaleCommand
    Command that converts all color (P3) images in the active session to grayscale.
    HelpCommand
    Command that displays a list of all supported commands with usage instructions.
    ImageMemento
    Stores a deep copy (snapshot) of a list of images, allowing undo functionality via the Memento pattern.
    LoadCommand
    Loads one or more image files into a single new session.
    Main
     
    MonochromeCommand
    Command that converts all grayscale (P2) and color (P3) images in the active session to monochrome (black and white).
    NegativeCommand
    Command for applying a negative (color inversion) effect to all images in the active session.
    NetPBMImages
     
    NetpbmLoader
    Utility class for loading NetPBM image files (PBM, PGM, PPM).
    NetpbmWriter
    Utility class for writing NetPBM images (PBM, PGM, PPM) to files.
    PBMImage
    Represents a PBM (Portable BitMap) image using the ASCII-based P1 format.
    PBMReader
    Reads PBM (Portable BitMap) image files in P1 format.
    PGMImage
    Represents a PGM (Portable Graymap) image in the P2 ASCII format.
    PGMReader
    Reads PGM (Portable Graymap) image files in P2 format.
    Pixel
    Represents a single pixel in an image.
    PPMImage
    Represents a PPM (Portable Pixmap) image using the ASCII-based P3 format.
    PPMReader
    Reads PPM (Portable Pixmap) image files in P3 format.
    Readers
     
    RotateCommand
    Command for rotating all images in the active session.
    SaveAsCommand
    Command for saving the first image in the current session under a new file name.
    SaveCommand
    Command for saving all images in the active session.
    Session
    Represents a user session containing a set of NetPBM images.
    SessionInfoCommand
    Command that prints information about the currently active image editing session.
    SessionManager
    Central manager for all image editing sessions in the application.
    SwitchCommand
    Command that switches the active session to a specified session ID.
    UndoCommand
    Command that reverts the last image modification in the active session.
